EFAmlpawlsglsminresStatisticians tend to prefer the maximum likelihood approach because of its well-defined statistical model. Sometimes this approach fails to converge, in which case the iterated principal axis option often works well..

r is a correlation matrix or a raw data matrix. nfactors specifies the number of factors to extract (1 by default). n.obs is the number of observations (if a correlation matrix is input). rotate indicates the rotation to be applied (oblimin by default). scores specifies whether to calculate factor scores (false by default). fm specifies the factoring method (minres by default).
